span></p><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; ma=
rgin: 0 0 1em 0;">That was a crazy claim to make in May 2020, but there wer=
e three reasons I thought it might be true:&#160;</p><ol style=3D"margin-to=
p: 0;"><li style=3D"margin-bottom: 4px; margin-left: 8px; margin-right: 0; =
margin-top: 4px;"><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height:=
 26px; margin: 0; margin-bottom: 0;"><span>It served as the previously-abse=
nt, </span><strong>globally-catalyzing event</strong><span> for the interne=
t generation.</span></p></li><li style=3D"margin-bottom: 4px; margin-left: =
8px; margin-right: 0; margin-top: 4px;"><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-si=
ze: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0; margin-bottom: 0;"><span>People acr=
oss the globe banded together, </span><strong>united by a common mission</s=
trong><span>: to fight the spread of this disease.</span></p></li><li style=
=3D"margin-bottom: 4px; margin-left: 8px; margin-right: 0; margin-top: 4px;=
"><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0=
; margin-bottom: 0;"><span>Having been forced to interact almost exclusivel=
y online for an extended period, people are creating new tools, processes, =
and social norms that </span><strong>make collaborating online more like co=
llaborating in-person</strong><span>.&#160;</span></p></li></ol><p style=3D=
"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;"><s=
pan>I thought that those three factors might be enough to precipitate the f=
irst global </span><strong>scenius, </strong><span>which musician Brian Eno=
 described as &#8220;the intelligence and the intuition of a whole cultural=
 scene. It is the communal form of the concept of the genius.&#8221;&#160;<=
/span></p><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; m=
argin: 0 0 1em 0;"><span>Think back to that time. There was fear and fighti=
ng, but most of it was focused on the pandemic and, in America, Trump. Outs=
ide of those two topics (and they&#8217;re very big ones, but concentrated)=
 the vibes online were incredibly positive. People experimented with new wa=
ys to connect, share information, have fun, and create online. Technology, =
from Zoom to mRNA, was viewed as a positive force. People, unlocked, </span=
><a href=3D"https://substack.com/redirect/18c77f79-407e-466c-af28-23139b95c=
5c2?u=3D16283549" rel=3D"" style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; text-decoration: underl=
ine;">often unwillingly</a><span>, from their old jobs, tried new things, a=
nd generally, people were supportive of whatever they pursued.&#160;</span>=
</p><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin:=
 0 0 1em 0;"><span>In a </span><a href=3D"https://substack.com/redirect/12f=
91cea-5601-4335-9ce6-993765add41e?u=3D16283549" rel=3D"" style=3D"color: #1=
a1a1a; text-decoration: underline;">2008 essay</a><span>, Kevin Kelly laid =
out the four factors that have historically nurtured scenius:</span></p><ul=
 style=3D"margin-top: 0;"><li style=3D"margin-bottom: 4px; margin-left: 8px=
; margin-right: 0; margin-top: 4px; mso-special-format: bullet;"><p style=
=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0; margin-b=
ottom: 0;"><strong>Mutual appreciation</strong><span> &#8212; Risky moves a=
re applauded by the group, subtlety is appreciated, and friendly competitio=
n goads the shy. Scenius can be thought of as the best of peer pressure.</s=
pan></p></li><li style=3D"margin-bottom: 4px; margin-left: 8px; margin-righ=
t: 0; margin-top: 4px; mso-special-format: bullet;"><p style=3D"color: #1a1=
a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0; margin-bottom: 0;"><str=
ong>Rapid exchange of tools and techniques</strong><span> &#8212; As soon a=
s something is invented, it is flaunted and then shared. Ideas flow quickly=
 because they are flowing inside a common language and sensibility.</span><=
/p></li><li style=3D"margin-bottom: 4px; margin-left: 8px; margin-right: 0;=
 margin-top: 4px; mso-special-format: bullet;"><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; =
font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0; margin-bottom: 0;"><strong>N=
etwork effects of success</strong><span> &#8212; When a record is broken, a=
 hit happens, or breakthrough erupts, the success is claimed by the entire =
scene. This empowers the scene to further success.</span></p></li><li style=
=3D"margin-bottom: 4px; margin-left: 8px; margin-right: 0; margin-top: 4px;=
 mso-special-format: bullet;"><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; =
line-height: 26px; margin: 0; margin-bottom: 0;"><strong>Local tolerance fo=
r the novelties</strong><span> &#8212; The local &#8220;outside&#8221; does=
 not push back too hard against the transgressions of the scene. The renega=
des and mavericks are protected by this buffer zone.</span></p></li></ul><p=
 style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1=
em 0;">All four were present on the early COVID internet, and to me, it fel=
t like we could finally unlock that idea of scenius from its geographic bou=
ndaries and bring it to a global scale.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a=
; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;"><span>But if you&=
#8217;ve watched </span><em>The Real World, </em><span>you&#8217;ll know th=
at the novelty and excitement of being thrown into unusual circumstances wi=
th a group of strangers fades quickly. Humans gonna human.&#160;</span></p>=
<p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0=
 1em 0;"><span>By like Episode 3, relationships and cliques and romances an=
